{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":873,"text":"After decades of research"},{"time":2930,"text":"and billions of dollars\nspent in clinical trials,"},{"time":6223,"text":"we still have a problem\nwith cancer drug delivery."},{"time":10586,"text":"We still give patients chemotherapy,"},{"time":12754,"text":"which is so non-specific"},{"time":14611,"text":"that even though\nit kills the cancer cells,"},{"time":17161,"text":"it kind of kills\nthe rest of your body, too."},{"time":20494,"text":"And yes, we have developed\nmore selective drugs,"},{"time":23974,"text":"but it's still a challenge\nto get them into the tumor,"},{"time":26701,"text":"and they end up accumulating\nin the other organs as well"},{"time":29641,"text":"or passing through your urine,"},{"time":31296,"text":"which is a total waste."},{"time":34389,"text":"And fields like mine have emerged"},{"time":36383,"text":"where we try to encapsulate these drugs"},{"time":38373,"text":"to protect them as they\ntravel through the body."},{"time":40950,"text":"But these modifications cause problems"},{"time":43827,"text":"that we make more modifications to fix."}]},{"cues":[{"time":46961,"text":"So what I'm really trying to say\nis we need a better drug delivery system."},{"time":51513,"text":"And I propose,"},{"time":52953,"text":"rather than using solely human design,"},{"time":55608,"text":"why not use nature's?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":58309,"text":"Immune cells are these versatile vehicles\nthat travel throughout our body,"},{"time":62187,"text":"patrolling for signs of disease"},{"time":64313,"text":"and arriving at a wound\nmere minutes after injury."},{"time":68000,"text":"So I ask you guys:"},{"time":70054,"text":"If immune cells are already traveling\nto places of injury or disease"},{"time":73459,"text":"in our bodies,"},{"time":74636,"text":"why not add an extra passenger?"},{"time":76966,"text":"Why not use immune cells to deliver drugs"},{"time":79917,"text":"to cure some of our biggest problems"},{"time":81903,"text":"in disease?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":84446,"text":"I am a biomedical engineer,"},{"time":86379,"text":"and I want to tell you guys a story\nabout how I use immune cells"},{"time":89404,"text":"to target one of the largest\nproblems in cancer."},{"time":92663,"text":"Did you know that over 90 percent\nof cancer deaths"},{"time":95194,"text":"can be attributed to its spread?"},{"time":96969,"text":"So if we can stop these cancer cells"},{"time":99258,"text":"from going from the primary tumor\nto a distant site,"},{"time":102356,"text":"we can stop cancer right in its tracks"},{"time":104856,"text":"and give people more of their lives back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108182,"text":"To do this special mission,"},{"time":109786,"text":"we decided to deliver\na nanoparticle made of lipids,"},{"time":112860,"text":"which are the same materials\nthat compose your cell membrane."},{"time":116733,"text":"And we've added two special molecules."},{"time":119952,"text":"One is called e-selectin,"},{"time":122153,"text":"which acts as a glue"},{"time":123453,"text":"that binds the nanoparticle\nto the immune cell."},{"time":127223,"text":"And the second one is called trail."},{"time":129740,"text":"Trail is a therapeutic drug\nthat kills cancer cells"},{"time":132420,"text":"but not normal cells."},{"time":134392,"text":"Now, when you put both of these together,"},{"time":137218,"text":"you have a mean killing machine on wheels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":143589,"text":"To test this, we ran\nan experiment in a mouse."},{"time":147276,"text":"So what we did was we injected\nthe nanoparticles,"},{"time":150365,"text":"and they bound almost immediately\nto the immune cells in the bloodstream."},{"time":154406,"text":"And then we injected the cancer cells\nto mimic a process"},{"time":157355,"text":"through which cancer cells\nspread throughout our bodies."},{"time":160530,"text":"And we found something very exciting."},{"time":163620,"text":"We found that in our treated group,"},{"time":166314,"text":"over 75 percent of the cancer cells\nwe initially injected were dead or dying,"},{"time":171118,"text":"in comparison to only around 25 percent."},{"time":173839,"text":"So just imagine: these fewer\namount of cells were available"},{"time":177045,"text":"to actually be able to spread\nto a different part of the body."},{"time":180181,"text":"And this is only after\ntwo hours of treatment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":182922,"text":"Our results were amazing,\nand we had some pretty interesting press."},{"time":187974,"text":"My favorite title was actually,"},{"time":190248,"text":"\"Sticky balls may stop\nthe spread of cancer.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":192886,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":194003,"text":"I can't tell you just how smug\nmy male colleagues were,"},{"time":198035,"text":"knowing that their sticky balls\nmight one day cure cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":201032,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":203354,"text":"But I can tell you they made\nsome pretty, pretty, exciting,"},{"time":206780,"text":"pretty ballsy t-shirts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208595,"text":"This was also my first experience\ntalking to patients"},{"time":212835,"text":"where they asked how soon\nour therapy would be available."},{"time":216279,"text":"And I keep these stories with me\nto remind me of the importance"},{"time":219448,"text":"of the science,\nthe scientists and the patients."}]},{"cues":[{"time":223809,"text":"Now, our fast-acting results\nwere pretty interesting,"},{"time":226374,"text":"but we still had one lingering question:"},{"time":228531,"text":"Can our sticky balls,"},{"time":230251,"text":"our particles actually attached\nto the immune cells,"},{"time":232958,"text":"actually stop the spread of cancer?"},{"time":235624,"text":"So we went to our animal model,\nand we found three important parts."},{"time":240615,"text":"Our primary tumors were smaller\nin our treated animals,"},{"time":243657,"text":"there were fewer cells in circulation,"},{"time":246199,"text":"and there was little to no\ntumor burden in the distant organs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250835,"text":"Now, this wasn't just a victory\nfor us and our sticky balls."},{"time":254737,"text":"This was also a victory to me"},{"time":256868,"text":"in drug delivery,"},{"time":258147,"text":"and it represents a paradigm shift,"},{"time":260102,"text":"a revolution --"},{"time":262330,"text":"to go from just using drugs,\njust injecting them"},{"time":265734,"text":"and hoping they go to the right\nplaces in the body,"},{"time":268211,"text":"to using immune cells\nas special delivery drivers in your body."},{"time":273975,"text":"For this example, we used two molecules,\ne-selectin and trail,"},{"time":277715,"text":"but really, the possibility\nof drugs you can use are endless."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281523,"text":"And I talked about cancer,"},{"time":283941,"text":"but where disease goes,\nso do immune cells."},{"time":287600,"text":"So this could be used for any disease."},{"time":290039,"text":"Imagine using immune cells\nto deliver crucial wound-healing agents"},{"time":294742,"text":"after a spinal cord injury,"},{"time":297474,"text":"or using immune cells to deliver drugs\npast the blood-brain barrier"},{"time":301895,"text":"to treat Parkinson's\nor Alzheimer's disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":305044,"text":"These are the ideas that excite me\nabout science the most."},{"time":308710,"text":"And from where I stand,\nI see so much promise and opportunity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312181,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313395,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}